<title type="html"><![CDATA[Hadith &amp; its Sciences • Re: Is There A Reward For Reading Hadeeth?]]></title>

<category term="Hadith &amp; its Sciences" scheme="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewforum.php?f=7" label="Hadith &amp; its Sciences"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1155&amp;p=1791#p1791"><![CDATA[
Al-Allamah AbdulHaqq Al-Hashimi رحمه الله, who was a teacher in the Haram and who gave Ijaazah in Hadith to Al-Imam Ibn Baaz رحمه الله had a daily portion of Sahih Al-Bukhari read in house and he would complete it every month.<br /><br />He would recite the verse in Surah Al-Ahzab...<br /><strong><em><span style="color: #FF0000">And remember what is recited in your houses of the verses of Allah and wisdom. Indeed, Allah is ever Subtle and Acquainted [with all things]. [33:35]</span></em></strong><br /><br />The scholars of tafseer have said that wisdom refers to what has been revealed to the Messenger ﷺ from the Sunnah. <br />Lets give importance to the Qur'an and ALSO the Sunnah of His Messenger ﷺ.<br />I remember reading this point in a book about the biography of the Shaykh in the library of Masjid Al-Nabawi.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=46555">SheikhAbdullah</a> — Tue Jun 30, 2020 3:46 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
