<title type="html"><![CDATA[Hadith &amp; its Sciences • Imam Ahmad On Fiqhi Issues And Giving The Proper Hadeeth It's Proper Share Of Priority]]></title>

<category term="Hadith &amp; its Sciences" scheme="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewforum.php?f=7" label="Hadith &amp; its Sciences"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1371&amp;p=1455#p1455"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">Imam Ahmad On Fiqhi Issues And Giving The Proper Hadeeth It's Proper Share Of Priority</span></strong><br />-----------------------------<br /><br />Imam Ahmad was once asked about a man who had memorized the Qur`an but did not do raf `al yadain and another man who did raf `al yadain but did not memorize the Qur`an, so who was more befitting to lead the people in prayers? Imam Ahmad said : “ The one who has memorized the Qur`an (is more befitting as it was the hadeeth of the prophet that the Imam should be the one who knew and understood Qur`an the most)and he should do raf `al yadain because it is the sunnah of the Messenger of Allah (Sallallaahu Alayhi Wasallam).<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">[Ref: Masail Imam Ahmad. For details see Shaykh Irshad ul-Haq Athari’s Maqalat Tarbiyat 212/177]</span></strong><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Sat Mar 25, 2017 4:45 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
